headline: UPS pilots and company resume contract talks, enlist federal mediator
summary: With fresh memories of the fatal crash of a freighter aircraft last month, UPS pilots and the company have resumed collective bargaining with the help of the National Mediation Board. The post UPS pilots and company resume contract talks, enlist federal mediator appeared first on FreightWaves.

headline: Long-Standing PostalAnnex Franchisee Renews Commitment to Serving Her Community in Fresno, CA
summary: Annex Brands, Inc., a leading franchisor in the packing, shipping, and office services industries, is proud to announce the renewal of a franchise agreement for the PostalAnnex location in Fresno, CA. This renewal reflects Shari Hamm's ongoing dedication to providing essential shipping and office services to the local community.

headline: Holiday Shipping Strains Intensify as FedEx and UPS Face Plane Groundings
summary: Douglas and Lee review how unexpected cargo-plane groundings at FedEx and UPS threaten holiday logistics and why supplier vulnerabilities can quickly cascade into earnings and stock performance.
